         <abstract>
            <p>According to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Spies1932Evagrius"/><citedRange>205</citedRange></bibl>, the Ethiopic version of Evagrius’ treatise only roughly corresponds to the Greek and Syriac versions. 
               It shares with them only the titles and main ideas. The (embedded) colophon states that the text was translated from Arabic during the reign of King <persName ref="PRS4428Galawdew"/>.
            </p>
         </abstract>
